                        <foliation>Foliation in Arabic numerals.</foliation>
                        <collation>Collated 19 January 1966. Latin translation of a list of the
                           first 35 sections (peraḳim) bound between folios 30 and 1, not included
                           in the foliation. Folios 1-30 in some disarray. M. Steinschneider,
                           Hebräische Übersetzungen, p. 741: “Falsch gebunden, mit leeren Blättern
                           (f. 15-18, 27-30), ergänzt (f. 11-14), teils doppelt geschrieben.“ A.
                           Neubauer, Catalogue, No. 2118: “At beginning are two leaves, containing a
                           portion of the supplied part of the preface.” Folios 11d and 12 (2nd
                           hand) = folio 25 (1st hand), folio 13 (2nd hand) = folio 26 (1st
                           hand).</collation>
